In recent years, the debate over whether younger people should be leaders of an organization has been a huge topic. While some argue that young people do not obtain sufficient experience, others contend that young people talks more naturally and more up to date.This essay will present my own perspective.

First and foremost, allowing a young people will be rewarded with 2 significant improvements which is young people getting experience and keeping the service up to date. The reason why it is not a wise choise to letting elderly become this crucial role, even though having more experience, is that it is better to create a stronger new generation instead of staying steady. Furthermore, young people have more opportunity for the organization and create miracles for it, meanwhile older people only have the power to keep the company or organization stable. Some people might disagree my opinion, because older people have more connections and getting better contracts. Even if this was counted as an advantage for the elderly, but it is still profits are greater that loss in my promising opinion

All in all, I believe that young people is a better choice for becoming the directors. Only by creating a better leader can allow the organization to keep active.